{"title_page": "Disease cluster", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\nA '''disease cluster''' is an unusually high [[Incidence (epidemiology)|incidence]] of a particular disease or disorder occurring in close proximity in terms of both time and geography.<ref>[http://www.atsdr.cdc.gov/HEC/CSEM/cluster/definition.html \"Definition of Clusters\"], ''Case Studies in Environmental Medicine (CSEM)'', [[Agency for Toxic Substances and Disease Registry]], [[U.S. Department of Health and Human Services]]</ref> Typically, when clusters are recognized, they are reported to [[public health]] departments in the local area. If clusters are of sufficient size and importance, they may be re-evaluated as [[outbreak]]s. The [[1854 Broad Street cholera outbreak|1854 cholera outbreak]] which occurred in London is a classic example of such a cluster.{{citation needed|date=October 2019}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Cancer cluster]]\n* [[Epidemiology]]\n* [[Cuzick\u2013Edwards test]]\n* [[Corby toxic waste case]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Epidemiology]]\n[[Category:Human diseases and disorders|Cluster]]\n\n\n{{disease-stub}}\n", "text_old": "A '''disease cluster''' is an unusually high [[Incidence (epidemiology)|incidence]] of a particular disease or disorder occurring in close proximity in terms of both time and geography.<ref>[http://www.atsdr.cdc.gov/HEC/CSEM/cluster/definition.html \"Definition of Clusters\"], ''Case Studies in Environmental Medicine (CSEM)'', [[Agency for Toxic Substances and Disease Registry]], [[U.S. Department of Health and Human Services]]</ref> Typically, when clusters are recognized, they are reported to [[public health]] departments in the local area. If clusters are of sufficient size and importance, they may be re-evaluated as [[outbreak]]s. The [[1854 Broad Street cholera outbreak|1854 cholera outbreak]] which occurred in London is a classic example of such a cluster.{{citation needed|date=October 2019}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Cancer cluster]]\n* [[Epidemiology]]\n* [[Cuzick\u2013Edwards test]]\n* [[Corby toxic waste case]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Epidemiology]]\n[[Category:Human diseases and disorders|Cluster]]\n\n{{disease-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Schwede66", "label": "safe", "comment": "date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease_cluster"}
